cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with a computational geometry problem of finding the minimum enclosing ball with outliers, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and has applications in various fields such as machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a randomized algorithm and discusses its theoretical analysis, which falls under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper applies the algorithm to handle outlier recognition on benchmark datasets, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
